The paper discusses online learning algorithms and their analysis, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of local sequential Rademacher complexities and associated algorithms suggests information theory (cs.IT) as another likely category. The paper also discusses matrix completion and transductive learning, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), respectively. Finally, the paper mentions prediction with static experts, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI).
